text: Mettingen is a municipality in the district of Steinfurt, in North Rhine- Westphalia, Germany. == Geography == Mettingen is about east of Rheine and west of Osnabrück. === Places close to Mettingen === Villages close to Mettingen are Recke in the west, Neuenkirchen, (Lower Saxony) in the north, Ibbenbüren in the south and Westerkappeln in the east. == Notable persons == The founders of the textile company C&A;, Clemens and August Brenninkmeyer, were born in Mettingen. Also Annika Suthe, participant of the 2004 Summer Olympics (javelin throw) was born there. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:Steinfurt (district)
